	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Paris - A French court handed down a three-year suspended jail term on Friday to the son of Equatorial Guinea's leader, Teodorin Obiang, after a landmark graft trial that lifted the lid on his playboy lifestyle. The 48-year-old, who is vice president of the West African country, was also given a suspended fine of $35 million dollars by judges after the trial in which he was accused of embezzlement and misusing public money. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  